<br>
As far as tanking, a warrior will always tank better due to not only increased hp, but also higher skill caps in various abilities.  Defensive/Evasive is not needed but does put the final nail in the coffin of knights main tanking boss raids.  Looking at overall balance, warriors may not be as highly regarded for exp fighting but they certainly make up for that in raiding usefulness.<br>
<br>
If all things hold, the new brells will not stack with the new beastlord buff(current versions of those two spells do not stack).  This makes the new brells very undesirable for almost all of the melee classes, why have 75 more hp when you can have 50 more att?<br>
<br>
Melee epics do suck.  Nearly all healer/casters epics are still useful to an extent.  But thats all due to the effect and not the ratio(which is primary importance for melee).  The bard epic falls more into the caster category though since its the effect you're using it for.  There is no reason you can't switch it out though for doing some more melee if thats your aim.<br>
<br>
Lastly, our new spell selection(paladin) is looking pretty weak.  With more mobs being unstunable one of our main spell choices is sliding into obscurity.  Our new buff spells are, predictably, not going to be used except in rare occcasions.  That leaves our useful spell selection down to a few spells, which has always been the case since Kunark.<br>
<br>
We've come a long ways since Kunark and thats definately a good thing, but if you see alot of complaints from the paladin direction its because verant appears to be making the same mistakes that were made in Kunark. That made this an extremely common occurance:  &quot;Hey there is a paladin LFG, you want to get him?  What are you kidding? We're better off without him.&quot;<br>
<br>
I remember trying to find a pickup group during kunark and it was nearly impossible.<br>
